16:48.286 --> 16:51.516
You break in here. you disrupt our lives.
you bind us hand-and-foot...

16:51.690 --> 16:54.920
...we damn near break our necks
hopping around the place...

16:55.093 --> 17:00.193
...and then when things
start getting sane again...

17:00.365 --> 17:03.555
...you break back in!

17:03.735 --> 17:06.464
-You don't have to raise your voice.
-He won't do it again.

17:06.637 --> 17:09.798
-I think he's got it out of his system.
-No. I haven't.

17:10.208 --> 17:13.867
I'm fed up. Nick.
and I want you to end this now!

17:14.479 --> 17:15.709
You're right.

17:15.880 --> 17:19.010
I probably cou|d've phrased that
differently. huh?

17:19.183 --> 17:21.413
It's gone far enough.

17:22.319 --> 17:24.409
One pull of the trigger...

17:24.954 --> 17:26.214
...and I'm history.

17:26.390 --> 17:28.920
-Don't do it. Nick!
-Okay.

17:32.129 --> 17:35.329
I couldn't shoot myself.
I'd probably screw it up anyway.

17:35.499 --> 17:37.759
Graze my temple
and hurt myself just bad enough...

17:37.935 --> 17:41.335
...to become a night manager
of a convenience store.

17:42.939 --> 17:46.099
Nick. you have a little trouble
dealing with pressure. don't you?

17:46.276 --> 17:48.236
It shows. huh?

17:48.411 --> 17:52.311
You know. Nick. I might have a way
to help relieve some of that pressure.

17:52.882 --> 17:56.792
If you turn yourself in.
I think I can get you a nice hospital stay.

17:57.220 --> 17:59.150
Three square meals a day.

17:59.322 --> 18:00.812
A little time to yourself.

18:03.125 --> 18:04.245
lS|GHS]

18:04.426 --> 18:06.946
Guess I'm just a loser. aren't I?

18:07.930 --> 18:10.370
I think you hurt his feelings.

18:10.532 --> 18:14.202
Mr. Rogers could hurt his feelings.

18:15.003 --> 18:16.943
Are you all right. Nick?

18:17.673 --> 18:19.203
Probably go to prison. huh?

18:19.841 --> 18:21.501
Probably.

18:21.942 --> 18:25.072
But you know. I think they got something
there that you might enjoy.

18:26.179 --> 18:29.109
-What?
-Yeah. what?

18:29.282 --> 18:30.312
Time.

18:31.685 --> 18:33.945
Time to be with yourself.

18:34.454 --> 18:36.484
Time to relax.

18:37.323 --> 18:38.883
Time to think.

18:41.927 --> 18:43.117
Hmm.

18:43.729 --> 18:45.719
That's actually kind of nice.

18:46.232 --> 18:47.862
Never had any time to myself.

18:48.033 --> 18:49.503
lSCOFFS]

18:50.269 --> 18:52.289
Even as a kid.

18:53.972 --> 18:58.432
My father pressured my brothers and I
into music.

18:59.576 --> 19:01.436
We formed a group when we were little...

19:01.612 --> 19:03.742
...and they went off
and made a lot of money.

19:04.915 --> 19:05.935
I hated music. though.

19:06.116 --> 19:08.946
You know. I just was never any good at it.
That's why they--

19:09.119 --> 19:12.319
[IN UNISON]
They kicked you out of the group.

19:12.489 --> 19:14.049
Yeah.

19:14.224 --> 19:17.854
I haven't spoken to Brian.
Dennis or Carl since.

19:19.762 --> 19:21.352
Yeah.

19:22.664 --> 19:25.074
Yeah. I'll do it. Sure.

19:25.901 --> 19:27.031
Why not?

19:27.202 --> 19:31.232
I mean. as you say. might not be so bad.

19:31.406 --> 19:33.306
I could maybe take up painting.

19:34.009 --> 19:36.839
Read all those books
I've been meaning to read.

19:37.012 --> 19:39.042
Catch up on my TV.

19:39.213 --> 19:41.203
[COUPLE MOANING OVER TV]

19:44.084 --> 19:45.784
Cable. huh?

19:51.926 --> 19:55.786
Sorry for all the trouble I caused you.
Thanks for all your help.

19:57.565 --> 19:59.465
Say. you know.
you two make a cute couple.

20:00.200 --> 20:02.730
We're not a couple.
We just work together.

20:02.903 --> 20:07.273
-Oh. you work together? Ooh. Trouble.
-Come on. Come on. Let's go.

20:12.112 --> 20:15.882
-You okay?
-Yeah. You?

20:17.217 --> 20:18.707
Well...

20:20.354 --> 20:22.324
...I guess I ought to be going.

20:22.489 --> 20:24.919
-Good night.
-Good night.

20:25.392 --> 20:26.662
Harry.

20:28.462 --> 20:30.832
You're welcome to stay if you want.

20:30.998 --> 20:33.398
It's not that I don't want to.

20:33.901 --> 20:34.931
lS|GHS]

20:35.102 --> 20:36.832
Yeah. but Nick might be right.

20:37.537 --> 20:40.837
It could make work awkward.

20:48.881 --> 20:50.321
It's dead.

20:51.883 --> 20:55.413
I guess we didn't need anything
hanging over our heads anyway. did we?

20:55.787 --> 20:57.477
Guess not.

21:04.296 --> 21:05.316
See you.

21:05.864 --> 21:07.564
See you.

21:14.773 --> 21:16.673
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

21:20.112 --> 21:21.672
Surprise.

21:23.047 --> 21:25.177
Borrow a cup of vermouth? Ha-ha-ha.

21:25.349 --> 21:28.249
Just kidding. Brought my own. Whoa.

21:28.719 --> 21:30.649
Hey. this is a nice place.

21:30.821 --> 21:34.191
Yeah. who needs the bother
of real wood. huh? Hah.

21:34.358 --> 21:35.378
Dan. what do you want?

21:35.559 --> 21:37.989
I figured you and Harry stayed
at the restaurant.

21:38.162 --> 21:39.632
You talked. had a few drinks--

21:39.797 --> 21:41.657
You figured you and I could have more...

21:41.832 --> 21:44.932
...until I got so drunk
I'd accept your invitation to the party...

21:45.102 --> 21:47.832
...without realizing
what a sleazy trick you had pulled.

21:48.472 --> 21:50.062
Yes.

21:51.474 --> 21:54.934
Look. Dan. it's been a long night.

21:55.111 --> 21:57.981
Harry and I came back here.
we walked in on a robber...

21:58.148 --> 22:02.208
...he had a gun. he tied us up.
and our lives were in danger.

22:04.154 --> 22:06.324
Harry was here?

22:06.989 --> 22:10.449
-Good night. Dan.
-Harry was here? With you?

22:10.626 --> 22:12.956
Besides the fact
that Harry was in my apartment...

22:13.128 --> 22:15.058
...you didn't hear a word I said.
did you?

22:15.230 --> 22:17.600
Yes. I did. And I am appalled.

22:17.766 --> 22:22.096
You spent a romantic evening
with someone you work with?

22:22.471 --> 22:24.001
And it wasn't me?

22:24.172 --> 22:25.902
lHUFFS]

22:28.875 --> 22:30.205
lGROANS]

22:39.486 --> 22:40.916
lS|GHS]

22:43.223 --> 22:46.063
BILLIE: I have had enough for one night.
and I am tired.

22:46.226 --> 22:48.626
Go away.

22:50.764 --> 22:51.994
[DOOR OPENS]

22:55.301 --> 22:57.171
It's my birthday.

23:06.312 --> 23:09.512
Sorry. I didn't have time to wrap it.

